  "texts": [
    "Research on emotion categorization has gained significance because of the proliferation of intelligent systems, including human-robot interactions.",
    "DL models, as highlighted in the study by Shehu et al. [113], have excelled in various classification tasks.",
    "However, their vulnerability to diverse attacks stems from their homogeneous representation of knowledge.",
    "Inspired by the ability of deep image priors to capture extensive image statistics from a single image, a robust defense method against adversarial examples is needed [78].",
    "Furthermore, Zhuo et al. [104] were motivated by the absence, to date, of proposed and analyzed adversarial attack and defense methods specifically tailored for industrial fault classification systems."
  ],
